# SMB HubSpot Nurture — The Pedowitz Group

A Node.js/Express service deployed on Render that generates personalized 10-email outbound nurture sequences for SMB HubSpot prospects. Contacts are enqueued from a HubSpot workflow, emails are written by the Claude API (as Jeff Pedowitz), and results are written back to HubSpot contact properties.

---

## Audience

- **Company size:** 10–500 employees
- **Platform:** Already using HubSpot
- **Titles:** VP/Director of Marketing, Demand Gen, RevOps, Marketing Ops, Sales
- **Signal:** Recent hiring in Marketing/Sales/RevOps roles
- **Pitch:** "You're investing in HubSpot. TPG makes sure that investment pays off."

---

## How It Works

1. A contact enters the HubSpot workflow and hits a **Custom Code step**
2. The custom code step POSTs the contact's data to the Render service `/enqueue` endpoint
3. The service adds the contact to an in-memory queue
4. Up to **10 concurrent workers** pick up jobs, scrape the prospect's website for personalization, call the **Claude API** to generate a personalized email, and write the subject line, HTML body, and plain text back to HubSpot contact properties
5. The `ai_email_step_status` property is updated throughout (`IN_PROGRESS` → `SENT` or `FAILED`)
6. The HubSpot workflow uses `ai_email_step_status = SENT` as the trigger to send the email and advance to the next step

---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `server.js` | Main Render worker service |
| `package.json` | Node.js dependencies |
| `hubspot_custom_code.js` | Paste into HubSpot workflow Custom Code step |

---

## Render Deployment

### Environment Variables
Set these in Render → your service → Environment:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `HUBSPOT_TOKEN` | Your HubSpot private app token |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Your Anthropic API key |

### Settings
- **Runtime:** Node
- **Build command:** `npm install`
- **Start command:** `node server.js`
- **Plan:** $7 Individual (or higher if running multiple nurtures simultaneously)

---

## Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/` | GET | Health check — returns queue length and in-flight count |
| `/dashboard` | GET | Live queue monitor (auto-refreshes every 5 seconds) |
| `/enqueue` | POST | Accepts a contact payload from HubSpot and adds to queue |

---

## HubSpot Setup

### Custom Properties Required (create before launching)
All properties are **contact** properties. Subject line and plain text = single-line text. Email body = multi-line text.

| Property Internal Name | Type | Description |
|------------------------|------|-------------|
| `tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_subject_line_em1–10` | Single-line text | Generated subject line per step |
| `tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_em1–10` | Multi-line text | Generated HTML email body per step |
| `tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_claude_text_em1–10` | Multi-line text | Plain text version (used for non-repetition) |
| `ai_email_step_status` | Single-line text | Processing status — shared across nurtures |

### Custom Code Step Setup
1. Paste `hubspot_custom_code.js` into the Custom Code step
2. Update `RENDER_URL` on line 3 with your actual Render service URL
3. Add all of the following as **Input fields** (Properties to include in code):

**Contact fields:**
`firstname`, `company`, `jobtitle`, `industry`, `website`, `hs_linkedin_url`, `numemployees`, `annualrevenue`, `description`, `web_technologies`, `hs_intent_signals_enabled`, `hs_analytics_num_page_views`, `hs_analytics_last_url`

**Prior email plain text (add all 10 even on step 1 — empty fields are handled gracefully):**
`tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_claude_text_em1` through `tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_claude_text_em10`

4. Add **Output fields:** `enqueue_status`, `queue_position`
5. Set `sequence_step` as a fixed input value per workflow branch (1 through 10)

### Workflow Structure
- **Enrollment trigger:** Contact meets SMB criteria (10–500 employees, using HubSpot, VP/Director title)
- **10 branches** — one per email step, each setting `sequence_step` = 1 through 10
- Each branch: Custom Code step → wait for `ai_email_step_status = SENT` → send email using the corresponding `tpg_smb_hubspot_nurture_em{N}` property → delay → next step

---

## Performance

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Concurrency | 10 simultaneous jobs |
| Anthropic tier | 50 RPM |
| Effective throughput | ~50 contacts/min |
| 7,000 contacts | ~2.5 hours |
| Domain scrape cache | 1-hour TTL (one scrape per domain) |
| Queue check interval | Every 500ms |

**Note:** If running this alongside other nurtures sharing the same Anthropic API key, the 50 RPM limit is shared across all services. Stagger start times by 3–4 hours to avoid simultaneous load.

